comment_data.body:
I always thought that the message and pause were really annoying as well. That's why I looked into it somewhat and wrote this basic patch (which may brake things but seems to work for ':!man man', with 'K' and for filtering with '!'):

```
diff --git a/src/nvim/ex_cmds.c b/src/nvim/ex_cmds.c
index 180a786..2e088ee 100644
--- a/src/nvim/ex_cmds.c
+++ b/src/nvim/ex_cmds.c
@@ -1212,7 +1212,6 @@ do_shell (
 )
 {
   buf_T       *buf;
-  int save_nwr;

   /*
    * Disallow shell commands for "rvim".
@@ -1263,43 +1262,22 @@ do_shell (
     msg_col = 0;
   }

-  if (autocmd_busy) {
-    if (msg_silent == 0)
-      redraw_later_clear();
-  } else {
-    /*
-     * For ":sh" there is no need to call wait_return(), just redraw.
-     * Also for the Win32 GUI (the output is in a console window).
-     * Otherwise there is probably text on the screen that the user wants
-     * to read before redrawing, so call wait_return().
-     */
-    if (cmd == NULL
-        ) {
-      if (msg_silent == 0)
-        redraw_later_clear();
-      need_wait_return = FALSE;
-    } else {
-      /*
-       * If we switch screens when starttermcap() is called, we really
-       * want to wait for "hit return to continue".
-       */
-      save_nwr = no_wait_return;
-      if (swapping_screen())
-        no_wait_return = FALSE;
-      wait_return(msg_silent == 0);
-      no_wait_return = save_nwr;
-    }
+  /*
+   * For external commands there is no need to call wait_return(),
+   * just redraw.
+   */
+  redraw_later_clear();
+  need_wait_return = FALSE;

-    starttermcap();             /* start termcap if not done by wait_return() */
+  starttermcap();             /* start termcap if not done by wait_return() */

-    /*
-     * In an Amiga window redrawing is caused by asking the window size.
-     * If we got an interrupt this will not work. The chance that the
-     * window size is wrong is very small, but we need to redraw the
-     * screen.  Don't do this if ':' hit in wait_return(). THIS IS UGLY
-     * but it saves an extra redraw.
-     */
-  }
+  /*
+   * In an Amiga window redrawing is caused by asking the window size.
+   * If we got an interrupt this will not work. The chance that the
+   * window size is wrong is very small, but we need to redraw the
+   * screen.  Don't do this if ':' hit in wait_return().   THIS IS UGLY
+   * but it saves an extra redraw.
+   */

   /* display any error messages now */
   display_errors();
```

The comment about starttermcap that I removed has me worried but I am not sure _why_ we really want to have to wait when we call starttermcap() (when looking at the function nothing stood out to me).

A possible disadvantage of this behavior is that some errors may not be reported anymore. If you hit 'K' on a identifier without a man page for example, you will only know that because the screen flickers and doesn't show the man page to you.

This patch basically is only to demonstrate that it is (easily?) possible to change the behavior. Further discussion is advised though. Making the behavior configurable would be an idea (I lean towards not interrupting the workflow with a pause and message in any case).
